    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/cointracker/cf76903b-1cc1-429b-9d46-6000dd13a4b5/application",
    "company": "CoinTracker",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "e3178cf07d482488",
    "department": "Legal",
    "description": "OVERVIEW\n\nCoinTracker https://www.cointracker.io/ makes cryptocurrency portfolio tracking and tax compliance simple. CoinTracker enables consumers and businesses to seamlessly track their cryptocurrency portfolio, investment performance, taxes, and more. We are a globally distributed team on a mission to enable everyone in the world to use crypto with peace of mind. Learn more https://www.notion.so/cointracker/CoinTracker-is-Hiring-7308c712493940a3b6e62257d283dad8 about our mission, culture, and hiring process.\n\n\n\nSOME THINGS WE’RE PROUD OF\n\n - 🛠️ Building foundational tools in the cryptocurrency space\n\n - 📄 Over 1M tax forms generated\n\n - 💲 $250B+ in cryptocurrency is tracked on CoinTracker (~over 5% of the entire crypto market)\n\n - 🤝 Partnered with Coinbase, H\u0026R Block, Intuit TurboTax, MetaMask, OpenSea, Phantom, Solana, and Uniswap\n\n - 🗺️ Founders: Jon https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonlerner/ previously built TextNow (200M downloads), Chandan https://www.linkedin.com/in/clodha/ was previously a product manager at Google \u0026 Google[x]\n\n - 💼 $100M+ venture capital raised from Accel, General Catalyst, Y Combinator, Initialized Capital, Coinbase Ventures, Kraken Ventures, Intuit Ventures, 776 Ventures, Balaji Srinivasan https://twitter.com/balajis, Claire Hughes Johnson https://twitter.com/chughesjohnson, Gokul Rajaram https://twitter.com/gokulr, Serena Williams https://twitter.com/serenawilliams, Zach Perret https://twitter.com/zachperret\n\n - 🌴 Awesome benefits https://www.notion.so/cointracker/Benefits-b5db95c6d3224ab1ae3a384048cbaee3\n\n\nYOUR MISSION\n\nServe as CoinTracker's first dedicated legal hire, leading the Legal function end-to-end — including commercial agreements, product counsel, corporate governance, and people matters — while enabling product velocity by providing risk-calibrated, business-oriented legal guidance.\n\n\nYOUR ONE-YEAR OUTCOMES\n\n - Trusted legal partner across the company. You proactively surface legal risks, provide clear guidance on product decisions, and are seen by the team as an accelerant — not a blocker.\n\n - All commercial agreements handled in-house. Partner agreements, customer contracts, and vendor agreements are drafted, negotiated, and managed internally at high quality.\n\n - Product development moves faster with legal clarity. Product and engineering teams have clear legal guardrails and timely guidance for launching new features and product lines.\n\n - Corporate and regulatory risk is well-managed. Governance, privacy, employment matters, and compliance are systematically addressed with risks surfaced early.\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\n - Lead the Legal function at CoinTracker across commercial, product, corporate, and people matters\n\n - Draft, negotiate, and manage all commercial agreements (partnership deals, customer contracts, vendor agreements, DPAs)\n\n - Partner with Product and Engineering to provide risk-calibrated legal guidance on new features, product lines, and international expansion\n\n - Manage corporate governance, equity matters, and board-related legal work\n\n - Handle people-related legal matters (employment agreements, policies, compliance)\n\n - Build legal infrastructure from scratch: contract templates, playbooks, and self-serve resources\n\n - Manage external counsel relationships for specialized matters (IP, regulatory, litigation)\n\n - Advise on crypto regulatory developments and their implications for CoinTracker's product\n\n\nWHAT WE LOOK FOR\n\n - Role-agnostic\n   \n   - Impact: Demonstrated ability to drive outsized business impact\n   \n   - Mission alignment: Strong personal conviction in crypto; hungry to make progress on our mission of enabling everyone to use crypto with peace of mind.\n   \n   - Trust: Say what you believe. Do what you say. Take ownership broadly\n   \n   - Communication: Clear and concise; able to distill complex legal concepts into plain language\n\n - Role-specific\n   \n   - 7+ years of legal experience post-law school with a mix of law firm and in-house\n   \n   - Strong commercial drafting and negotiation skills — can build contracts from scratch\n   \n   - Experience serving as product counsel, partnering with Product/Engineering teams\n   \n   - Demonstrated ability to provide risk-calibrated advice that enables (not blocks) product development\n   \n   - Comfortable operating in ambiguous regulatory environments\n   \n   - Experience at a high-growth technology company\n   \n   - Self-starter who thrives with autonomy\n\n - Nice to have\n   \n   - Top-tier law firm background (Goodwin, Cooley, Wilson Sonsini, Latham, etc.)\n   \n   - Experience at a crypto or fintech company\n   \n   - Familiarity with crypto regulatory landscape (SEC, FinCEN, state regulations, MiCA)\n   \n   - Background in data privacy (GDPR, CCPA)\n\nThe starting salary for this position is between $201,000 - $236,000 USD. Candidate's location does not impact the posted salary range.\n\nThe actual compensation offered will be based on a variety of job-related factors including relevant skills, education, and experience. This position also includes significant equity in CoinTracker and benefits like medical, dental, vision, 401(k), life insurance, and PTO.",
